{"build_type":"library","description":"Channel B submit-side primitive. Any in-world requester that inherited the portal (region in g_portal_region_base, request eventfd fd3, response eventfd fd4) uses this to run a request through the kernel without a Linux pipe: write the request length at region[0] and the request JSON at region+8, ring the request eventfd (fd3), block on the response eventfd (fd4), then read the response length at region[0] and return the response cstring at region+8 (NUL-terminated). Additive Channel B; does not touch Channel A.","module_name":"transmit-request-through-portal-region-awaiting-reply","package_name":"transmit-request-through-portal-region-awaiting-reply","function_definitions":{"transmit-request-through-portal-region-awaiting-reply":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"request","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"unused","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"one","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":1},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"three","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":3},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"four","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":4},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"eight","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":8},{"instruction_type":"global_read","dest":"base","name":"g_portal_region_base"},{"instruction_type":"function_invocation","invocation_name":"determine-string-character-sequence-length","invocation_arguments":[{"kind":"var","value":"request"}],"result_assignment_variable":"reqlen","result_type":"i64"},{"instruction_type":"array_write","base":"b